body:
So I&#039;m in S3, tryin to slowly become a better player and not worrying about winning but more about become better. Slowly but surely I&#039;m climbing so I&#039;m happy with that. 


What I&#039;ve noticed though, and this confuses the hell outa me, is that I&#039;m S3 but most of the players in my matches are above s3. Last match for example had only one S3 person, me. We had three S1&#039;s, Two S2&#039;s, someone in their promos, one S4, and a Gold5.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}} 

I get that mmr trys to make it balanced and puts teams together with roughly the same overall MMR rating or whatever. 

What I don&#039;t get is why I have to face-off against literally no one in my ladder. In Tennis for example, I played it in High-school (made it to state too :D) If I wanted to move up the ladder on our team, I had to play the person directly above me. I couldn&#039;t go against the number one dude and then rank above the person barely higher than me. I had to play and beat that dude first and move up. Then our coach could mix things up if he saw we kept beating people way higher on the ladder. 

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}} 

Anyways, even though my mmr might put me against people above my ladder, I feel like I should still go up against the people my rank. In S3, I should go against S3 players until I&#039;m S2, and if I&#039;m winning so much more than usual, after the promotional wins the game should then put me where I should belong. (Which I believe it already does but you still have to play against people higher than you to even get to that point.) 

I dunno I feel like the system is both choosing who I go against as an individual but my individual results are team based. 


{{sticker:sg-zephyr}} 

Meh, hopefully someone can help me out with this, also looking forward to the ranking system change in 2019, hopefully that fixes this shit.
